  "texts": [
    "Both studies reported increased water quantity.",
    "Respondents in Elgert's study noted using rainwater for almost six months of the year, meaning family members (primarily women) reduced the number of trips made to the public water points compared to those without the rainwater harvesting system.",
    "Half of the participants in Glasgow et al. 's study reported water availability throughout the year.",
    "In Guatemala, rainwater was primarily used for drinking and cooking, whilst laundry was done at public water points to conserve rainwater [53].",
    "In Carricoao, respondents used rainwater for drinking, cooking, bathing, laundry and cleaning [46]."
  ],
